# 📊 Phase 2 - Excel Dashboard

## Overview

After completing the SQL analysis, I connected my MySQL database to Microsoft Excel using ODBC and Power Query. The main goal of this phase was to build a fully dynamic Business Intelligence dashboard that automatically updates whenever the database changes.

The dashboard is designed in such a way that after updating the data in MySQL, I only need to click **Data → Refresh All**, and all the tables, Pivot Tables, charts, KPI cards, and slicers are updated automatically without any manual work.


